My friends and some of relatives who USED to frequent the club kept saying that this particular bouncer was rude, unpolished, and should not be working in a high end club like Sammy's.

He pretends to be the management, but you can see that he has no customer service experience at all. This bouncer has some serious issues, that need to be addressed by management. There are a lot of complaints on social media about this particular bouncer and management seem to be hiding their heads in the sand.

I might also add that some of the girls are less than average. I found it very difficult tipping girls that I didn't think that should be allowed to strip dance on a public stage.

Sammy's used to be a classy and very customer friendly club in Birmingham, not anymore. A lot of my friends and relatives have recommended that I try "The Furnace club". I will not be going back to Sammy's any time soon, that's for sure. If you are spending your hard earned money you at least expect good customer service and a friendly environment. A bouncer is the first staff member you get to see and therefore, a creepy and rude one is very telling of the outlook of the club in general.

name: Lauren Brooke
text: My husband and I went here for a date night while we were on vacation. I enjoy going to the old school steak restaurants, so I picked Nolan's because of their Instagram posts. I'm glad I did. We had a great experience and it was exactly the type of restaurant I was looking for. Service was great. We ordered the steer butt and the Cajun grilled prime rib, both were excellent. The meat was cooked perfect, baked potato and salad were good. It is typical prices for a nicer steak house, so don't expect a cheap dinner. We enjoyed the live music and old school vibe.

name: Russell Strong
text: Nolans is a great fine dining restaurant. We had no wait when we went at about 7:30, the service was exceptional. They do not seat people who come in looking like they just woke up from bed, you do have dress nice. The food was great, had the New York Strip steak, grilled to perfection. Prices are high, but with the food as good as it is and the wait staff being on point, price doesn't matter.

text:
We love this place!!  We booked their private room for my son-in law and daughter's wedding reception back in June 2014 without visiting the restaurant.  I have to admit I was a little worried since we are from Texas and not having any idea what the food would be like or what the restaurant would look like but to my wonderful surprise it was all fabulous!!  Most of our guest had steak and it was perfect and plenty.  The staff was very professional and kind, whatever we needed they supplied.  We had almost 50 guest and plenty of room to visit.  We were also allowed to come earlier than scheduled to decorate.  I would say an absolute thumbs up for this place!!  When we come back for vacation we will visit again.

It may have beeen textbook salesmanship, I don't know but I ended up buying a new pipe with accessories and he threw in a bag of tobacco of my choice and a cool little box to store it in for free. All of that, and I still came out much cheaper with a better quality pipe than I purchased just the day before. Not only was the staff friendly but the customers who were there, all of which the salesman new by name, drew me in and not only helped me pick out a good starter tobacco but showed me how to pack it correctly and gave me a bag or two of their own to try.
